The Vibe.Market community is vibrant but not without friction, as seen in heated X exchanges where the team defends against accusations of favoring AI art or undercutting traditional artists. 

 Critics label it "grifting," but supporters highlight its role in reviving fun, liquid trading over illiquid NFTs. 

@metrogoooning

 The team responds transparently, emphasizing inclusivity and education (e.g., suggesting Grok for learning), while promoting positive vibes through alerts, giveaways, and creator shoutouts. 

 This raw interaction builds loyalty, with users forming "tribes" around themes like Cabal. 

